nning this week, every Saturday Srijan presents a discussion on the winners of Nobel Prize for Literature. To begin with, it has chosen Gao Xingjian, winner of the literature prize for 2000. His masterpiece, Soul Mountain, would be read and discussed.				 																FELICITATION				 																																	 June 12 at the Durbar Hall, Great Eastern Hotel; 5 pm: Felicitation to Somnath Chatterjee, who has been appointed Speaker of the Lok Sabha. The programme will be presided over by Jyoti Basu and the state Assembly Speaker H.A. Halim will grace the occasion.				 																VARIETY				 																																	 June 13 at Heramba Chandra College; 10 am onwards: Heramba Chandra College Alumni Association organises a day-long programme  a prelude to the golden jubilee celebrations of South City group of colleges.				 																																	 June 13 at Oxford Bookstore; 5 pm: A magical show for children.				 																																	 June 13 at University Institute Hall; 6 pm: Shinjan, Institution of Bharata Natyam amp; Creative Dance presents patriotic songs, creative dance by the younger ones, Tagores Rituranga, Karna-Kunti Sambad through dance, nostalgic dance creations and dances accompanied by revolutionary poems. Direction: Kohinoor Sen Barat and Sujoy Thakur.				 																 WORKSHOP				 																																	 June 12 onwards at 188/90 Prince Anwar Shah Road; 12 noon - 2 pm: Thoughtshop Foundation begins its Peer Telecounselling Course. Based on persona growth and self development, the course enables participants to help other young people and enhance their own communication skills. Details at 24176128/29.
